day we lowered for a pod of four or five whales, and my boat fastened to one of 
them; a regular circus horse he was, too, that went milling and milling round 
so, that my boat’s crew could only trim dish, by sitting all their sterns on 
the outer gunwale. Presently up breaches from the bottom of the sea a bouncing 
great whale, with a milky-white head and hump, all crows’ feet and 
